## DO NOTs — never violate these rules

**Visual / theme**
- Do NOT use white, light gray, or any light background color anywhere in the app.
- Do NOT use Inter, Roboto, or `sans-serif` system fonts — use Outfit only.
- Do NOT use purple or violet as the primary accent color. That is GameHub's color. Use Steam blue `#1E9FFF`.
- Do NOT enable Material3 DynamicColor / Monet color extraction. It overrides the carefully chosen palette.
- Do NOT add card elevation drop shadows. Use `strokeColor` border (`#FFFFFF18`) for the flat dark aesthetic instead.
- Do NOT fetch the 460×215 Steam header image for the 2:3 portrait cards — they stretch badly. Use 600×900 portrait capsule images.

**Kotlin / adapter**
- Do NOT call `notifyDataSetChanged()` anywhere. Always use `submitList()` through DiffUtil. The only acceptable exception is when the user switches between grid and list display modes.
- Do NOT load images inside `onBindViewHolder` payload partial updates — partial rebinds must only update the specific field that changed (progress value, status chip color, favorite icon).

**Performance configs**
- Do NOT leave `WINEDEBUG` enabled in any build. Debug logging kills CPU performance.
- Do NOT set `DXVK_HUD` in production. Only use it during local debug sessions.
- Do NOT run `vm.max_map_count` sysctl on the Android host OS. It must run **inside the Linux container** only.
- Do NOT remove the `ulimit -n 1048576` line before Wine launches. ESYNC requires it or Wine will crash.
- Do NOT remove the `VKD3D_DISABLE_EXTENSIONS` ray tracing disablement. Adreno has no hardware RT; leaving it wastes CPU.
- Do NOT simplify or shorten the DXVK/VKD3D/Wine explanatory comments. They exist so future contributors understand why each setting is present.
